            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28461",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please read the FAQ http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFFAQ\/Forms\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-26T05:38:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-26T05:38:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28462",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "FYI:\nAn non-existing form element has nothing to do with an not uploaded file.\n\nThe exception is thrown because the form element was not found.\nThe ignoreNoFile option handles only not uploaded files on existing form elements.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-26T05:45:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-26T05:45:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28463",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "???\nThe form element exists and is showed to user but not mandatory. It is an element among others.\nWhen the user doesn't add the file to the complete form and when i call isValid on this form, i received this exception. Is it normal?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-26T07:26:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-26T07:26:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28464",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Only because the form exists it does not mean that it is rendered correct.\n\nYou have not shown any related code for reproduction.\nIs the hidden field displayed... is the element named correct...  and so on...\n\nAs already said... you will get this exception when the element is not rendered correct... rendering is not viewing... you don't see all necessary data.\n\nThe FAQ points you to the problem... wrong usage of setDecorator.\nAnd yes... in this case the problem is normal.. as for all other form elements which are in need of correct decorators like image, captcha and others.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-26T08:54:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-26T08:54:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28468",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "My decorators are:\n{code}\n$this->addDecorator('File')    \/\/ <- I have the File decorator\n     ->addDecorator('Errors')\n     ->addDecorator('Label', array('class' => 'ui-accordion-header ui-helper-reset ui-state-default ui-corner-all label'))\n     ->addDecorator('HtmlTag', array('tag' => 'div' , 'class' => 'element'));\n{code}\n\nMy creation of file element is:\n{code}\n$form->addElement('file',\n        'ctrl_sip_b',\n        array('label' => 'Fichier de contr\u00f4le matrice B' ,\n                'required' => false));\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-26T09:14:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-26T09:14:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28481",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This was resolved by adding:\n{code}\n$form->setAttrib('enctype', Zend_Form::ENCTYPE_MULTIPART);\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-26T09:58:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-26T09:58:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28483",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The problem was that the form had not set \"enctype\".\n     ->setAttrib('enctype', Zend_Form::ENCTYPE_MULTIPART)\nsolves the problem.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-26T10:00:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-26T10:00:07.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
